The seven storey warehouse burnt down on the evening of Friday, 20 March, 1903.
&gt;&gt;&gt; <a href="http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/14536046" rel="nofollow">The Sydney Morning Herald, Saturday 21 March 1903, pp. 11-12.</a> &lt;&lt;&lt;
Keep reading, the account goes on beyond the highlighted segment. Seems to have been a spectacular fire. This of course means we've narrowed the date range for the photo: 1900 - 20/3/1903. Much narrower than the <a href="http://www.slv.vic.gov.au/pictoria/gid/slv-pic-aab69737/1/b28021" rel="nofollow">State Library of Victoria</a> and <a href="http://www3.photosau.com/cos1/scripts/ExtSearch.asp?SearchTerm=040532" rel="nofollow">City of Sydney Archives</a> circa dates of 1901 and 1910.
